<div type="definition">
<p>DISSATISFIED IN-RELATION-TO one's SELF:own PAST ACTION.BECAUSE one BELIEVES them to have been WICKED.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The current general word for regret of one's actions is huǐ 悔, whereas the current general word for regretting past experience is hèn 恨.　LH: 鳥與人異，謂之能悔。</p>
<p>2. Jiù 疚 refers to specifically moral regret.</p>
<p>3. Xí 惜 refers to emotional and sentimental regret.</p>
        </div>
